The IRS has made strides in improving computer security, but vulnerabilities persist, risking taxpayer data theft.
Efforts to catch unauthorized file access are limited, prompting the need for better safeguards.
Vice President Al Gore emphasizes the importance of protecting privacy in online activities, proposing initiatives to enhance data security.
Identity theft cases, like Santner's elaborate scheme, highlight the growing threat.
Victims face challenges clearing their names and credit records.
Legislation aims to combat identity theft, urging caution in sharing personal information and advocating for secure practices to prevent fraud.
